Text.Value: As if I needed the reminder. I'll take my chances on the surface.

EditorData.stateContext: Skickpit is whispering, leaning closer conspiratorially

Text.Value: Then shh - keep it low. Don't let them hear you.
Hey now. What's with the hostility?
So like I said: piss off.
That's the thing - I'm not really a True Soul.

EditorData.logicalname: Did not claim to be a True Soul earlier

Text.Value: It's pronounced: 'I tremble afore your awful majesty.'
Leave.
Off with you. They'll get suspicious.
You do look the sort. Well - if you're craving blood, better theirs than mine.
Listen, I'm here to help. Play along.
I'll need you to repeat that.
Whatever sick game this is I want nothing to do with it. Get the hells away from me.
Hang on. You sure you want to pick a fight with these gnomes? They've got bigger problems than us.
Go where you want. I've done enough for you.
It doesn't matter. Do you want my help or not?
But you better finish the job, 'cause I'll be the one to suffer if you don't.
Figures. You want blood? Those pisspots will spill plenty.
My name's [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53]. I'm not really a True Soul.
Nah - not one who freed me from slavers, anyway. You did me right.
Shit. You did it.
Hah! Thulla was mad as a rutting badger, but she weren't a friend of any True Soul.
Say that to me one more time, and I'll gut you.
Damn it - just when I thought you half decent.
Ahem. Ain't you hearin' me, prick-hole? Piss off to every last hell!

EditorData.NodeContext: Suddenly loud, so nearby duergar will overhear him.

Text.Value: I heard the pisspot - you're a True Soul, same as Nere.
Think this through. Strike a slave, and its owners will not simply stand by.
You want to play hero, Blade? I'm not complaining.
Cool it. You think you'd be any less mouthy if slavers took you hostage?
You're a True Soul, all right. You look it. You smell it.
I'm working so hard to be a nice person these days but you're really trying my patience.
Fine - let's say I believe you. You want to kill these peckers, I'm not complaining.
Won't be needing this poison, now that you've offed the pricks. Bet you'll find it handy, though.
Piss off.
Last chance. You want me to kill your slavers or not?
Free? Glory to Ironhand! I'll join the others.
You're all the same. I'd sooner spit in your shitter than trust a single damn word.
Well, you did me right once, so you earned my trust twice.
Careful - attack a slave, and you might have to answer to the slave master.
Leave.
I can call you other silly names, True Soul. Like arserag, or shitepot.
Piss off yourself.
Now - why in the hottest hells would a True Soul be helping me?
Beldron is taking the others across the lake. Wait for them there.

EditorData.logicalname: Gnomes freed, didn't talked to, haven't left

Text.Value: Go find somewhere to hide - wait for things to cool down.
I heard the pisspot - you're a True Soul, same as Nere. Traitor to your kind.
Hold on. This fellow may deserve it, but I don't think the duergar will appreciate you hurting the merchandise.
The others are free. Meet them at the dig site.

EditorData.logicalname: Gnomes free and alive, haven't left.

Text.Value: Fine, fine - I'm not looking for more trouble.
Beldron's safe, then? Thank Ironhand. I'll make my way over.
I'm not with these arseholes.
So listen close. I won't say it again.
What now?
I know a place, cross the lake. Should be safe.
Free? From your mouth, I hope. Go on, then - split them open. I'm not gonna stop you.
I'm in the mood for a little slaughter.
Prepare to strike.
Trust me. Would a gnome steer you wrong?
And who asked for help? Why don't you - hold on. You're talking true, aren't you?
They're thick and scrappy, no doubt. If fighting's your vice, I'm not gonna stop you.
*A shred of doubt gives you pause. Attack the gnome, and his owners are sure to defend him.*
No, you don't understand. Thulla sent me to save you.
Beldron took the others across the lake. You should join them.
Grymforge is even more dangerous. Stay at your own peril.
No one should serve a master. You deserve to be free.
Is that so? Well listen close, True Soul - I've got a new tune to whistle.
Take the lift to the surface.
The Blade of... well, shit. You're really him, aren't you?
Piss. The drugh. Off.
What can I say? I just love killing.
They call me the Blade of Frontiers. I'm not a True Soul - I can help you.
Just do it, before I cut out that profane tongue of yours.
No need to be rude. I'm on your side.
My side? I heard the pisspot. You're a True Soul, same as Nere.
Attack the gnome.
Fine. You want to spill their guts, I won't stand in the way.
The curse is cleared. You'll be perfectly safe.
That's the best comeback you've got? Amateur.
You look like you're in trouble. Surely I can help you.
You're not going to let him talk to you like that, are you?
Piss off to every hell.
Didn't you hear me the first time? Piss. Off.
They look like they'd put up a good fight.
Shit - up there? Forget it. I hear the land's cursed clear to Moonrise.
What about 'piss off' do you - hold on. You aren't just talking shit, are you?

EditorData.NodeContext: Voice lowers when he realises player is offering to help

Text.Value: Down here I know what I'm dealing with. Up there, not so much. Got a better idea?
Figure it out yourself.
Shit. You aren't just talking from your arse, eh?
Really? Drugh yes. Glory to Ironhand!

EditorData.NodeContext: Absolutely relieved / Drugh = an epithet. DROOG

Text.Value: Better that than chance the damn curse. You got a plan C?
You might be a shithead. But I'm grateful.
How about we show these slavers what deep gnomes are made of, instead?
Cleared - just like that, huh? Well I'm not taking the chance. Any other ideas?
You want to help me? Then open those ears and listen close.
You're a good one. I won't forget it.
MOVE. I WASN'T ASKING.
I go where I like. Move.
I told you. I'm not really a True Soul.

EditorData.logicalname: Claimed no to be TS earlier

Synopsis: Skickpit has a foul mouth to match the duergar. He runs their errands for them and brings them drinks. You can ask if he wants freed, attack him, or leave him be.
